N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 15 ยง 19.6 - Uncollected taxes

State Regulations

The Commissioner of Motor Vehicles agrees to furnish the
city of New York with names of registrants against whom a tax was stated but
not collected. If the tax was not collected because of a change of address made
at the time of application for renewal, the Commissioner of Motor Vehicles
further agrees to supply the city of New York with old and new addresses of
said registrants. Notes
